<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880623-0066 </DOCNO><HL> Arkansas Best Offer Begins </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ABZ </CO><IN> TNM TRA </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Best Acquisition Corp. began an offer to buy all 10.1 million Arkansas Best Corp. common shares for $26 a share and $50 million of convertible subordinated debentures for $1,002.31 for each $1,000 principal amount.    After maneuvering for weeks to avoid the acquisition bid, Arkansas Best, a Fort Smith, Ark., trucking firm, Friday agreed to the $316 million transaction. Best Acquisition was formed by Kelso andamp; Co., an investment banking firm based here.    The offer was made in an advertisement in today's Wall Street Journal.    (Revised WSJ June 23, 1988)</TEXT></DOC>